frontends: accelerate multicast received over a PPPoE WAN (IPv4 + IPv6)

The multicast connection_process bails (NF_ACCEPT) for any ARPHRD_PPP
ingress device, lumping PPPoE in with genuine L3 tunnels (the stock
"TODO: Add support for multicast over tunnels" skip). On a PPPoE WAN
(e.g. Telekom IPTV / MagentaTV) the multicast source ingresses pppoe-wan,
so the flow is dropped before the MFC lookup and the NSS mc_rule is never
created - routed multicast offload is impossible.

PPPoE is not a generic tunnel for ECM: ECM_INTERFACE_PPPOE_ENABLE is set
(kmod-pppoe selected), the multicast 'from' interface hierarchy already
resolves a PPPoE session (PX_PROTO_OE). So in the cmn connection_process
(both v4 and v6) allow an ARPHRD_PPP ingress through the tunnel guard when
it is a PPPoE session (ecm_interface_mac_addr_get_pppoe), while still
skipping non-PPPoE PPP (PPTP/L2TP). Same-subnet and LAN-to-LAN multicast
(non-PPP ingress) are untouched.

The IPv4 NSS frontend already has the ECM_DB_IFACE_TYPE_PPPOE case in its
from-interface walk that sets NSS_IPV4_MC_RULE_CREATE_FLAG_INGRESS_PPPOE;
the IPv6 frontend was missing it (a PPPoE source iface hit default: and the
INGRESS_PPPOE flag was never set), so add the mirrored case to the v6
from-walk. The PPPoE egress/to-walk was already symmetric in both families.

Gated behind ECM_INTERFACE_PPPOE_ENABLE. The NSS firmware's ingress-PPPoE
decap for multicast (the mc_rule carries only the INGRESS_PPPOE flag plus
src_interface_num=base-eth, no ingress pppoe if_num) is unproven and must
be validated on real hardware; a fw NACK is harmless (ECM falls back to
the host path).

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

--- a/frontends/cmn/ecm_multicast_ipv4.c
+++ b/frontends/cmn/ecm_multicast_ipv4.c
@@ -560,6 +560,7 @@ unsigned int ecm_multicast_ipv4_connecti
 	bool br_dev_found_in_mfc = false;
 	int protocol = (int)orig_tuple->dst.protonum;
 	__be16 *layer4hdr = NULL;
+	bool in_dev_is_pppoe = false;
 
 	if (protocol != IPPROTO_UDP) {
 		DEBUG_WARN("Invalid Protocol %d in skb %px\n", protocol, skb);
@@ -581,9 +582,23 @@ unsigned int ecm_multicast_ipv4_connecti
 	 *
 	 * Acceleration for multicast packet which is sent to
 	 * or received from VxLAN tunnel net device should be skipped.
+	 *
+	 * Exception: a PPPoE ingress (e.g. IPTV multicast arriving over a
+	 * PPPoE WAN) IS accelerable - the multicast interface hierarchy and
+	 * the NSS mc_rule handle a PPPoE 'from' interface when
+	 * ECM_INTERFACE_PPPOE_ENABLE is set. Allow ARPHRD_PPP through only
+	 * when it is a PPPoE session; keep skipping non-PPPoE PPP tunnels
+	 * (PPTP/L2TP).
 	 */
+#ifdef ECM_INTERFACE_PPPOE_ENABLE
+	if (in_dev->type == ARPHRD_PPP) {
+		uint8_t pppoe_node_addr[ETH_ALEN];
+		in_dev_is_pppoe = ecm_interface_mac_addr_get_pppoe(in_dev, pppoe_node_addr);
+	}
+#endif
 	if ((in_dev->type == ECM_ARPHRD_IPSEC_TUNNEL_TYPE) ||
-	    (in_dev->type == ARPHRD_SIT) || (in_dev->type == ARPHRD_PPP) ||
+	    (in_dev->type == ARPHRD_SIT) ||
+	    ((in_dev->type == ARPHRD_PPP) && !in_dev_is_pppoe) ||
 	    (in_dev->type == ARPHRD_TUNNEL6) ||
 	    (netif_is_vxlan(in_dev)) || (netif_is_vxlan(out_dev))) {
 		DEBUG_TRACE("in_dev: %px, in_type: %d, out_dev: %px, out_type: %d",
--- a/frontends/cmn/ecm_multicast_ipv6.c
